OSX Keybindings:



All apps:
cmd:/    -fullscreen active app
cmd+Q  -quit active app


Terminal:
cmd+N  -open new window
cmd+T  -add new tab
cmd+]   -next tab
cmd+[   -previous tab
opt+cmd+/    -close tab or ignore command on last tab
cmd+shift+W    -close window

Chrome:
cmd+N   -open new window
cmd+T   -add new tab
cmd+]   -next tab
cmd+[   -previous tab
opt+cmd+/    -close tab or close window on last tab
cmd+shift+W    -close window
cmd+L       -focus address bar and highlight text if any
cmd+R -refresh page
opt+cmd+]  -navigate forward in history
opt+cmd+[  -navigate backward in history


Sublime:
cmd+N    -add new tab(cmd+T)
cmd+]   -next tab
cmd+[   -previous tab
opt+cmd+/    -close tab or close window on last tab
cmd+shift+W   -close window
cmd+shift+N   -close all tabs but not the window(cmd+shift+/)
opt+cmd+S   -save all
cmd+F -find
cmd+P -goto
cmd+e -find selected text
fn+F5 -refresh folders


Sublime\Python:
opt+cmd+/  -toggle comments for cursor line or multiline selection


sublime key map to OSX conversions:
super == cmd
ctrl == ctrl
alt == opt


Preferences > Key Bindings > User:

Change in sublime prefs from:
[
    { "keys": ["f5"], "command": "refresh_folder_list" },
    { "keys": ["super+]"], "command": "next_view" },
    { "keys": ["super+["], "command": "prev_view" },
    { "keys": ["alt+super+/"], "command": "close" }
]

setting for close all tabs without closing the window
{ "keys": ["super+shift+w"], "command": "close_all" }
